n{{Fb a footer   |s=107297|h=14526|l= 5681|a= 9754|pr= 7176|u=23 February 2020 |source=[http://data.j-league.or.jp/SFTD14/search?endDayNum=8&competition_year=2020&competition_frame=2 J. League Data]|notes=<sup>\u2020</sup> Last year in [[J1 League]]\u3002<sup>\u2021</sup> Last year in [[J3 League]]\u3002|date=2020\u5e742\u6708}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2020 in Japanese football}}\n{{Japanese Club Football|group=second}}\n\n[[Category:J2 League]]\n[[Category:Football in Japan]]\n[[Category:2020 in Asian second tier association football leagues|Japan]]\n[[Category:Sports events postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|J2]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football league season\n| competition = Meiji Yasuda J2 League\n| winners = \n| relegated = none (for season 2020 only)\n| matches = 11\n| total goals = 15\n| league topscorer = [[Kazuki Nishiya]]<br>(3 goals)\n| biggest home win = \n| biggest away win = \n| highest scoring = \n| longest wins = \n| longest unbeaten = \n| longest winless = \n| longest losses = \n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance = \n| attendance = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason = [[2019 J2 League|2019]]\n| nextseason = ''[[2021 J2 League|2021]]''\n| updated = 2020/02/23\n| season = 2020\n| dates = \n}}\nThe '''2020 J2 League''', also known as the {{Nihongo|'''2020 [[Meiji Yasuda Life|Meiji Yasuda]] [[J2 League]]'''|2020 \u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547dJ2\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0|2020 Meiji Yasuda Seimei J2 R\u012bgu|lead=yes}} for sponsorship reasons, will be the 28th season of [[J2 League]], the top Japanese professional league for association football clubs, since its establishment in 1993. The league will start on 21 February 2020. For this season, the league will have season break to avoid clash with [[2020 Summer Olympics|Olympics 2020]] starting from June to August.<ref>{{cite web|last=Orlowitz |first=Dan |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/sports/2019/12/18/soccer/j-league/j-league-season-include-olympic-break/#.XjRW3h6yQ0M/ |title=J. League season to include Olympic break |publisher=The Japan Times |date= |accessdate=2020-01-31}}</ref>\n\n== Effects of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic ==\nOn February 25, all J.League matches until March 15 were postponed in response to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite press release|date=2020-02-25|url=https://www.jleague.jp/release/post-63079/|title=2020J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547dJ1\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u7b2c2\u7bc0\uff5e\u7b2c4\u7bc0 \u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547dJ2\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u7b2c2\u7bc0\uff5e\u7b2c4\u7bc0 \u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547dJ3\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u7b2c1\u7bc0\uff5e\u7b2c2\u7bc0 J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0YBC\u30eb\u30f4\u30a1\u30f3\u30ab\u30c3\u30d7 \u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8\u7b2c2\u7bc0\uff5e\u7b2c3\u7bc0 \u958b\u50ac\u5ef6\u671f\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|publisher=\u65e5\u672c\u30d7\u30ed\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0|accessdate=2020-02-28|language=Japanese}}</ref> After that,it was announced that it would be postponed until March 29.<ref>{{Cite press release|date=2020-03-12|url=https://www.jleague.jp/en/news/article/16824/|title=J.LEAGUE to Extend Suspension of Matches|publisher=Official|accessdate=2020-03-21}}</ref> On March 19, the J.League announced no relegation would take place for the 2020 season, with the J1 League expanding to 20 clubs for the 2021 season. <ref>{{Cite press release|date=2020-03-19|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/sports/2020/03/19/soccer/j-league/j-league-skip-relegation-schedule-threatened-coronavirus/|title=J. League to skip relegation as schedule threatened by coronavirus|publisher=The Japan Times|accessdate=2020-03-21}}</ref>  On March 25, announced that it would be Suspended April 3 to May 6.<ref>{{Cite press release|date=2020-03-25|url=https://www.jleague.jp/en/news/article/16881/|title=J.LEAGUE Further Extends Suspension of Matches|publisher=Official|accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nOn April 3, decided to starting over the official game schedule, which aims to gradually resume J3 from April 25, J2 from May 2, and J1 from May 9. Note that, considering a new schedule in the future, but it will resume it at least one month later and later in the month.<ref>{{Cite press release|date=2020-04-04|url=https://www.jleague.jp/news/article/16921/|title=\u518d\u958b\u306e\u65e5\u7a0b\u306f\u767d\u7d19\u306b\u3002\u7b2c5\u56de\u65b0\u578b\u30b3\u30ed\u30ca\u30a6\u30a4\u30eb\u30b9\u5bfe\u7b56\u9023\u7d61\u4f1a\u8b70\u4f1a\u898b\u30ec\u30dd\u30fc\u30c8|publisher=\u65e5\u672c\u30d7\u30ed\u30b5\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0|accessdate=2020-04-04|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n== Clubs ==\n{{J2 League map 2020}}\n\nAfter spending only one season in J2 [[Kashiwa Reysol]] became champions and have been promoted to [[2020 J1 League]] along with [[Yokohama FC]]. [[2019 J3 League]] champions [[Giravanz Kitakyushu]] and second place [[Thespakusatsu Gunma]] entered the league as promoted teams, replacing [[Kagoshima United FC|Kagoshima United]] and [[FC Gifu]] who were relegated to [[2020 J3 League]]. Those teams that qualified for promotion playoffs in 2019 were unable to defeat their opponent and thus remain in [[2020 J1 League]] season.\n\n[[Giravanz Kitakyushu]] return to J2 after spending 3 seasons in J3, while [[Thespakusatsu Gunma]] return after spending one single season.\n\nMeanwhile,  [[Matsumoto Yamaga F.C|Matsumoto Yamaga]] and [[J\u00fabilo Iwata]] will join [[2020 J2 League]] as relegated teams from [[2019 J1 League]] having placed 17th and 18th respectively.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Club Name\n!Home Town\n!Stadium\n!Capacity\n!Last season\n!licence\n|-\n| [[Albirex Niigata]]\n| [[Niigata, Niigata|Niigata]] & [[Seiro, Niigata|Seiro]], [[Niigata Prefecture|Niigata]]\n| [[Denka Big Swan Stadium]]\n| 42,300\n| J2 (10th)\n| J1\n|-\n| {{sort|Avispa|[[Avispa Fukuoka]]}}\n| [[Fukuoka City]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka]]\n| [[Level5 Stadium]]\n| 22,563\n| J2 (16th)\n| J1\n|-\n|[[Ehime FC]]\n| All cities/towns in [[Ehime Prefecture|Ehime]]{{efn|centering on [[Matsuyama, Ehime|Matsuyama]]}}\n| [[Ningineer Stadium]]\n| 20,000\n| J2 (19th)\n| J1\n|-\n|[[Fagiano Okayama]]\n|All cities/towns in [[Okayama Prefecture|Okayama]]{{efn|centering on [[Okayama, Okayama|Okayama]], [[Kurashiki, Okayama|Kurashiki]], [[Tsuyama, Okayama|Tsuyama]]}}\n| [[City Light Stadium]]\n| 20,000\n| J2 (9th)\n| J1\n|-\n|[[Giravanz Kitakyushu]]\n|[[Kitakyushu]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka]]\n|[[Mikuni World Stadium Kitakyushu]]\n|15,066\n|[[Image:Arrowupgreen.png]] Promoted from J3 <small>(Champions)</small>\n| J1\n|-\n|[[JEF United Chiba]]\n|[[Chiba, Chiba|Chiba]] & [[Ichihara, Chiba|Ichihara]], [[Chiba Prefecture|Chiba]]\n| [[Fukuda Denshi Arena]]\n| 18,500\n| J2 (17th)\n| J1\n|-\n| [[J\u00fabilo Iwata]]\n| [[Iwata, Shizuoka|Iwata]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka]]\n| [[Yamaha Stadium]]\n| 15,165\n| [[Image:Arrowdownred.png]] Relegated from J1 <small>(18th)</small>\n| J1\n|-\n|{{sort|Sanga|[[Kyoto Sanga FC|Kyoto Sanga]]}}\n|Cities/towns in [[Kyoto Prefecture|Kyoto]]{{efn|[[Kyoto]], [[Uji, Kyoto|Uji]], [[Joyo, Kyoto|Joyo]], [[Kyotanabe, Kyoto|Kyotanabe]], [[Muko, Kyoto|Muko]], [[Nagaokakyo, Kyoto|Nagaokakyo]], [[Kizugawa, Kyoto|Kizugawa]], [[Kameoka, Kyoto|Kameoka]], [[Nantan, Kyoto|Nantan]], [[Kyotanba, Kyoto|Kyotanba]], [[Fukuchiyama, Kyoto|Fukuchiyama]], [[Maizuru, Kyoto|Maizuru]], [[Ayabe, Kyoto|Ayabe]]}}\n| [[Sanga Stadium by Kyocera]]\n| 21,600\n| J2 (8th)\n| J1\n|-\n|[[FC Machida Zelvia|Machida Zelvia]]\n|[[Machida, Tokyo|Machida]], [[Tokyo]]\n| [[Machida Athletic Stadium]]\n| 10,600\n| J2 (18th)\n| J1\n|-\n| [[Matsumoto Yamaga]]\n| Cities/towns in [[Nagano Prefecture|Nagano]]{{efn|[[Matsumoto, Nagano|Matsumoto]], [[Azumino]], [[Yamagata, Nagano|Yamagata]], [[Shiojiri, Nagano|Shiojiri]], [[Omachi, Nagano|Omachi]], [[Ikeda, Nagano|Ikeda]], [[Ikusaka, Nagano|Ikusaka]], [[Minowa, Nagano|Minowa]], [[Asahi, Nagano|Asahi]]}}\n| [[Sunpro Alwin]]\n| 20,396\n| [[Image:Arrowdownred.png]] Relegated from J1 <small>(17th)</small>\n| J1\n|-\n|{{sort|HollyHock|[[Mito HollyHock]]}}\n|Cities/towns in [[Ibaraki Prefecture|Ibaraki]]{{efn|[[Mito, Ibaraki|Mito]], [[Hitachinaka]], [[Kasama]], [[Naka, Ibaraki|Naka]], [[Omitama]], [[Ibaraki, Ibaraki|Ibaraki]], [[Shirosato, Ibaraki|Shirosato]], [[Oarai, Ibaraki|Oarai]], [[Tokai, Ibaraki|Tokai]]}}\n| [[K's denki Stadium Mito]]\n|  12,000\n| J2 (7th)\n| J2\n|-\n| {{sort|Montedio|[[Montedio Yamagata]]}}\n| All cities/towns in [[Yamagata Prefecture|Yamagata]]{{efn|centering on [[Yamagata, Yamagata|Yamagata]], [[Tendo, Yamagata|Tendo]], [[Tsuruoka, Yamagata|Tsuruoka]]}}\n| [[ND Soft Stadium]]\n|  20,315\n| J2 (6th)\n| J1\n|-\n| [[Omiya Ardija]]\n| [[Saitama, Saitama|Saitama]], [[Saitama Prefecture|Saitama]]\n| [[NACK5 Stadium Omiya]]\n|  15,500\n| J2 (3rd)\n| J1\n|-\n| [[Renofa Yamaguchi FC|Renofa Yamaguchi]]\n| All cities/towns in [[Yamaguchi Prefecture|Yamaguchi]]\n| [[Yamaguchi Ishin Park Stadium]]\n|  20,000\n| J2 (15th)\n| J1\n|-\n|[[FC Ryukyu]]\n|All cities/towns in [[Okinawa Prefecture|Okinawa]]{{efn|centering on [[Okinawa, Okinawa|Okinawa]]}}\n| [[Tapic Kenso Hiyagon Stadium]]\n| 25,000\n| J2 (14th)\n| J1\n|-\n|[[Tochigi SC]]\n|[[Utsunomiya]], [[Tochigi Prefecture|Tochigi]]\n| [[Tochigi Green Stadium]]\n|  18,025\n| J2 (20th)\n| J1\n|-\n|[[Thespakusatsu Gunma]]\n|All cities/towns in [[Gunma Prefecture|Gunma]]{{efn|centering on [[Kusatsu, Gunma|Kusatsu]] and [[Maebashi]]}}\n|[[Shoda Shoyu Stadium Gunma]]\n|15,253\n|[[Image:Arrowupgreen.png]] Promoted from J3\uff082nd\uff09\n| J1\n|-\n| {{sort|Vortis|[[Tokushima Vortis]]}}\n| All cities/towns in [[Tokushima Prefecture|Tokushima]]{{efn|centering on [[Tokushima, Tokushima|Tokushima]], [[Naruto, Tokushima|Naruto]], [[Mima, Tokushima|Mima]], [[Matsushige, Tokushima|Matsushige]], [[Itano, Tokushima|Itano]], [[Aizumi, Tokushima|Aizumi]], [[Kitajima, Tokushima|Kitajima]]}}\n| [[